Filter iDigBio results by scientific name

Source: R/filter_fix_names.R
filter_fix_names.Rd

The filter_fix_names() function filters a data frame for relevant results, based on the scientific name given. Some downloaded results from iDigBio might contain occurrences of other species that have "notes" mentioning the desired species. Hence, this function looks for relevant results that are actually occurrences of the desired species.

Usage

filter_fix_names(df, synonyms_list, filter = "fuzzy", accepted_name)

Arguments

df

Data frame with name column to be fixed.

synonyms_list

A list of synonyms for a species.

filter

The type of filter to be used--either "exact" or "fuzzy".

accepted_name

The accepted scientific name for the species.

Value

Returns data frame with filtered results.

Details

This function requires no additional packages.

Examples

data %>% filter_fix_names(c("Asclepias curtissii", "Asclepias aceratoides", "Asclepias arenicola", "Oxypteryx arenicola", "Oxypteryx curtissii"), filter = "exact")
